Example of method used via the DSpace CLI to retrieve this information:

```
coll = DSpace::CLI::Collection.find_by_handle("88435/dsp01th83m2429")

items = coll.get_all_items

items.each do |i|
    date_val = i.submitter.getLastActive.nil? ? 'NA' : i.submitter.getLastActive.toLocalDateTime.to_s.split("T").first 
    puts "#{i.submitter.full_name},#{i.submitter.email},#{date_val}"
end 
```

I used [this collection](https://github.com/pulibrary/pdc_discovery/blob/main/config/collections.csv) to get all of the handles needed.
